1 (ii) a member of the Board of Commissioners, designated by the
2 Executive Director;
3 (4) one member of the Montgomery County Historical Society, designated
4 by the Society;
5 (5) one member who has professional experience in issues of discrimination
6 or housing, appointed by the Montgomery County Council;
7 (6) one member who has professional experience in issues of discrimination
8 or housing, appointed by the Montgomery County Executive;
9 (7) one member of the Montgomery County Racial Equity and Social
10 Justice Advisory Committee, designated by the Committee;
11 (8) the Pastor of the Emory Grove United Methodist Church; and
12 (9) one member who is a former resident of the Emory Grove community
13 and lived in the community at any time between 1960 and 1985, designated by the Pastor
14 of the Emory Grove United Methodist Church.
15 (c) The Director of the Montgomery County Office of Human Rights shall serve
16 as the chair of the Task Force.
17 (d) The Montgomery County Office of Human Rights shall provide staff for the
18 Task Force.
19 (e) (1) The Task Force shall hold its first meeting not later than July 1, 2025,
20 and meet at least quarterly thereafter.
21 (2) The Task Force may hold additional meetings as determined necessary
22 by the chair.
23 (f) A member of the Task Force:
24 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Task Force; but
25 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
26 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
27 (g) The Task Force shall:
28 (1) review and analyze the displacement of residents of Emory Grove under
29 the urban renewal program carried out from 1960 through 1985 in order to:

