1 (i) determine the basis for the development of the Emory Grove
2 urban renewal program and the guidelines and execution of the program, including how
3 property was acquired or purchased from landowners;
4 (ii) analyze the way urban renewal was administered in Emory
5 Grove;
6 (iii) analyze the decisions to use the urban renewal program in
7 Emory Grove and the equity impacts of the program;
8 (iv) analyze the guidelines and execution of the urban renewal
9 program in Emory Grove, including the purchase of property from landowners and the
10 demolition of homes;
11 (v) determine the basis for the purchase of property from
12 landowners in Emory Grove and identify the details of land purchases, including the
13 purchase prices and purchase agreements; and
14 (vi) analyze the plan for providing replacement properties or new
15 homeownership for the displaced residents of Emory Grove and the equity impacts of the
16 plan, including proposed dates to provide new replacement properties and incentives or
17 benefits for previous landowners; and
18 (2) if deemed appropriate by the Task Force, recommend remedies for past
19 inequities in the purchase of land by Montgomery County through the urban renewal
20 program in Emory Grove from 1960 to 1985, including methods for determining eligibility
21 and providing compensation, such as benefits for former landowners and incentives for
22 construction projects.
23 (h) (1) On or before December 15, 2025, the Task Force shall submit an interim
24 report of its findings and recommendations to the Montgomery County Council, the
25 Montgomery County Executive, and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
26 Article, the Montgomery County delegation to the General Assembly.
27 (2) On or before December 15, 2026, the Task Force shall submit a final
28 report of its findings and recommendations to the Montgomery County Council, the
29 Montgomery County Executive, and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
30 Article, the Montgomery County delegation to the General Assembly.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
32 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of 2 years and 1 month and, at the end of June
33 30, 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the General Assembly, shall be
34 abrogated and of no further force and effect.

